The Decorator Pattern is a Structural Design Pattern that allows you to add new functionality to an object dynamically without modifying its existing code.

Why Do We Need Decorator Pattern?

Suppose a bank has a Basic Bank Account.

Some customers also want:

SMS Alerts
Email Alerts
Reward Points
Insurance

Instead of creating classes like:

Banking Example
................................
Step 1: Component Interface
................................
interface BankAccount {

    void openAccount();
}

Step 2: Concrete Component
................................
class SavingsAccount implements BankAccount {

    @Override
    public void openAccount() {

        System.out.println("Savings Account Opened");
    }
}

Step 3: Abstract Decorator
................................
abstract class AccountDecorator implements BankAccount {

    protected BankAccount account;

    public AccountDecorator(BankAccount account) {
        this.account = account;
    }

    @Override
    public void openAccount() {
        account.openAccount();
    }
}

Step 4: Concrete Decorators
................................

SMS Alert
................................
class SMSAlertDecorator extends AccountDecorator {

    public SMSAlertDecorator(BankAccount account) {
        super(account);
    }

    @Override
    public void openAccount() {

        super.openAccount();

        System.out.println("SMS Alert Activated");
    }
}

Email Alert
................................
class EmailAlertDecorator extends AccountDecorator {

    public EmailAlertDecorator(BankAccount account) {
        super(account);
    }

    @Override
    public void openAccount() {

        super.openAccount();

        System.out.println("Email Alert Activated");
    }
}

Step 5: Client
................................
public class Main {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        BankAccount account =
                new EmailAlertDecorator(
                    new SMSAlertDecorator(
                        new SavingsAccount()));

        account.openAccount();
    }
}

Output
................................
Savings Account Opened
SMS Alert Activated
Email Alert Activated


